ThinkPart(
    type='think',
    think='Now I have a comprehensive understanding of the PR. Let me check a fe
w more files to ensure I haven\'t missed anything critical, then I\'ll compile t
he review report.\n\nKey things I\'ve noticed so far:\n\n1. **MessageDto status 
enum in OpenAPI** - The `im.yaml` defines `status` enum as `[sent, read]` but th
e actual backend code uses `sent` as default and the PRD mentions states like `s
ending`, `sent`, `delivered`, `read`. The OpenAPI contract doesn\'t include `del
ivered` which is used in the Gateway. Also, the mobile code uses `sending`, `fai
led`, `sent`, `delivered`, `read`.\n\n2. **BDD test for push notification** - Th
e `im_real_time_message_delivery.steps.js` has a placeholder assertion for push 
notifications that always passes with `assert.ok(true, ...)`. This is an empty i
mplementation.\n\n3. **SendMessageDto content validation** - The DTO marks `cont
ent` as `@IsOptional()` but the service requires it for both text and image type
s. However, `@ValidateIf((o) => o.type === "text")` means content is optional fo
r image type, but the service checks `if (dto.type === "image" && !dto.content)`
which throws. There\'s a semantic issue: for `system` type, content is also requ
ired but DTO doesn\'t enforce it.\n\n4. **Widgetbook registration** - The new de
sign system components (`SwChatBubble`, `SwChatInputBar`, `SwConversationListIte
m`, `SwChatMessageList`) don\'t seem to be registered in `widgetbook/main.dart`.
\n\n5. **Maestro flow issues** - Looking at `.maestro/flows/im/includes` - it\'s
a symlink to `../../includes`. Let me check if this is correct.\n\n6. **AuthServ
ice Redis client creation** - `AuthService` creates its own Redis client (`this.
redis = new Redis(redisConfig)`) instead of using the shared `RedisModule` provi
der. This violates the NestJS coding规范 about shared resources.\n\n7. **Matchin
gService onModuleDestroy** - `MatchingService` calls `this.redis.quit()` on modu
le destroy, but the Redis client is a shared singleton from `RedisModule`. This 
could disconnect Redis for all modules.\n\n8. **Conversation list pagination cur
sor** - `getConversations` uses `updated_at` as cursor, but per `api.md`, compos
ite cursor `(updated_at, id)` should be used for high-concurrency lists.\n\n9. *
*OpenAPI contract vs actual code** - `MessageDto.status` enum in `im.yaml` is `[
sent, read]` but the actual message lifecycle includes `sending`, `sent`, `deliv
ered`, `read`. The frontend uses `sending` and `failed` as local-only statuses, 
but the backend should document `sent` and `read` at minimum. Actually, looking 
more carefully, the backend stores `sent` and the gateway emits `delivered` - bu
t `delivered` isn\'t in the OpenAPI YAML.\n\nLet me check a few more things befo
re writing the report.',
    encrypted=None
)
