    think='Now I have a thorough understanding of the PR. Let me compile my find
ings into a structured review report.\n\nKey issues I\'ve identified:\n\n**Block
ing:**\n1. **AuthService creates its own Redis client instead of using shared Re
disModule** - This violates `nestjs.md` section on "跨模块共享资源" which explic
itly prohibits modules from creating their own Redis clients. The `AuthService` 
constructor does `this.redis = new Redis(redisConfig)` instead of injecting the 
shared `REDIS_CLIENT`. This causes connection duplication and makes the AuthServ
ice bypass the shared singleton.\n\n2. **MatchingService.quit() disconnects shar
ed Redis** - `MatchingService` implements `OnModuleDestroy` and calls `this.redi
s.quit()` in `onModuleDestroy()`. Since `RedisModule` provides a shared singleto
n Redis client, when `MatchingService` is destroyed (e.g., during hot reload or 
module shutdown), it will disconnect Redis for ALL modules including IM, Auth, e
tc. This is a critical shared resource management bug.\n\n**Major:**\n3. **OpenA
PI MessageDto.status enum is incomplete** - `im.yaml` defines `status` enum as `
[sent, read]`, but the backend Gateway emits `message:delivered` events, and the
mobile code handles `sending`, `sent`, `delivered`, `read`, `failed` statuses. T
he contract doesn\'t accurately reflect the actual message status lifecycle. Als
o, `last_login_at` migration might affect existing functionality.\n\nWait, let m
